review_blob: pours very pale clear yellow,  lots of lacing, light flavor but might as well eat a had full of grass

Its growing on me as I drink it.  At first it seemed a little bland with no delivery,  as I continue through the bottle, the flavors are seeming to become more alive and I look forward to the next drink.

Rye bread smell really comes through; Deep clear copper brown color with a thick 1 finger head;  Enjoyable taste and a little on the sweet side; hints of caramel, chocolate; the more I drank, the more I liked it.
Pours a clear yellow/orange color with very light head; fruity nose; citrus & pine flavors with a bitter finish.
Pours a clear brown color; nice white head; caramel aroma and taste; slight dry / bitter finish.
Pours a Clear golden color with a pale white head; Fruity aroma and taste with the right amount of hop flavor; crisp but slight bitterness in the finish.

Pours a dark reddish brown with floral aroma and full head that lasts and creates nice lacing. The taste is Carmel and fruit with slight licorice.  No significant after taste, very drinkable and one Ill drink again.
Pours a clear light copper; not much head; very drinkable with grainy flavor, little sweetness and a Crisp finish. Surprised how much I liked it.
beer_name: Two Brothers Long Haul Session Ale

review_blob: Clear dark brown with very think cream head and lasting lacing; chocolate malt aroma and flavor with a nutty background; hint of coffee with a light bitter finish.
Pours a clear dark brown with a small cream head and lacing that lasts around the edge.  Toasty aroma and flavor with a burnt finish.  Not on my list as it is for many others.
Poured a light clear yellow with little head or aroma;   Not much wheat character for me and even seemed a little thin.
Pours a yellow gold with small head;  sweet aroma and taste with spices; found it different and unusual; one I will try again.
Pours a dark caramel and has slight caramel aroma;  Slightly sweet with a dry after taste.
Poured a hazy amber with thin head; somewhat light light on the pallet but a lingering aftertaste.

Poured yellow slightly cloudy with a small off-white head; Fruity aroma; Medium hoppiness with citrus overtones; slightly bitter with long after taste. A decent IPA for those of us who like them a little less strong.
Pours a hazy dark caramel with a small light cream head that dissipates quickly to lace ring that lasts.  Some caramel in the aroma,  A little sweet and again caramel in flavor.  Works for me.
Pours a pale lemonade color with a bright white great head that dissipated quickly; somewhat sweet aroma; taste of fruit & coriander, refreshing and very light with good carbonation.
Bottle; pours a clear slightly pale copper color;  Small off white head with little lacing.  An earthy flavor with sweet malt background;  slight dry finish.
Bottle; Pours a cloudy yellow with lasting lace; has a citrus flavor, good carbonation and a somewhat dry finish.
Bottle; pours a dark walnut color with 1 finger head; a smokey/roasty slightly sweet taste; nice mouth feel finishes watery; not as strong as expected for such a dark beer.

Bottle; pours a very light pale yellow; Thin head with no lacing; slight aroma with even less flavor.  Liked the comment that it would be water if it didnt have carbonation.  Disappointed since I like so many Shiner beers,  too bad I got one more from my sampler pack.
Bottle; pours a copper color with a medium lasting head and lasting lacing;  Aroma of bread; Taste is a dull kind of cereal which becomes somewhat a bitter dry lasting finish.
Bottle; pours a light gold color without much head.  A very light IPA with a watery finish;  a beer I would have liked more in my earlier beer drinking days
Bottle pours a cloudy Yellow with a short head that disappeared quickly.  Aroma is light as is the taste that is refreshing.  A good wit for the newcomers to the style.
Bottle; Pours a medium, semi-cloudy amber with a light head. A light IPA with a nice finish.  If you have a friend who has never had an IPA, a good one to start them off on.
Draft at Old Chicago; served with medium head; aroma of pumpkin spices; off flavor not the pumpkin flavor I was after.
12oz bottle from fall variety pack; cloudy copper color; smokey aroma and taste; good carbonation; finishes with slight bitter smokey flavor.
Poured a reddish amber with a light head;  Aroma of pumpkin & spice;  Sweet pumpkin flavor; good carbonation; not much of a finish.
12oz bottle; pours a dark brown coke-a-cola color; thin head that dissipates quickly; aroma of malt; smooth with slight sour after taste.
12oz bottle; pours clear golden with nice head and continued lace; good carbonation; aroma of spice & malt; has a roasted type flavor with clean finish.
12oz bottle; pours a golden copper with little head but good lacing and carbonation.  Very drinkable and smooth without any distinguishing flavors or aftertaste.
12 oz bottle;  Pours a clear golden color with 2 finger pale cream head that melts to a lace covered top; Not much aroma;  good carbonation; very hoppy; slight bitter finish.
12oz bottle; pours a reddish amber; a light head with lasting lace around the rim; taste is sweet; light carbonation; slight bitter finish.
12oz bottle, typical mass produced lager; gold color; thin white head; unimpressive metallic taste

12 oz bottle; pours a cloudy deep amber; 1 finger off white head that lingered; hoppy aroma; flavor not as bitter as I expected, citrus, caramel, hoppy finish.  I like this one and why I have learned to like pale ales.
beer_name: Two Brothers The Bitter End Pale Ale

review_blob: 12 oz bottle; Pours slightly cloudy pale yellow/gold color; 2 finger head that faded quickly to a lace ring; Floral aroma with some spice; nice carbonation; Very light flavor, little citrus; somewhat dull finish.  Have not had many Kolsch style so dont know how to compare well.  Would drink it again.

12oz bottle; pours a deep dark walnut color with thin head; sweet Chocolate aroma; sweet flavor of dark coffee and burnt toast; finish with a slight bitter taste.  Usually dont like porter but enjoyed this.
12oz bottle; pours a clear golden yellow with a thin head and long lasting lacing; flavors of citrus, very hoppy; finish is a dry, bitter and long lasting.  Not a favorite IPA for me.
12oz bottle; color is a cloudy yellow; very thin head; citrus aroma; taste of citrus with a light finish; very drinkable.
12oz bottle; pours an orange amber ;1 finger head with good lacing and plenty of carbonation; slight metalic background and slight bitter finish.

12oz bottle; pours light golden orange with a white head and lingering lace;  aromas of grains; off flavors of grass, grain & hops; good carbonation; somewhat dry citrus bitter finish;  not what I want for a summer beer.
12oz bottle from sample case; pours deep clear copper color with 1 finger thick & lasting head; hoppy aroma; some citrus, hops with bitter lasting finish
12oz bottle; pours clear bright golden color with small white head that fades quickly; An earthy/grainy flavor; high carbonation; dry finish.
12oz bottle; poured a copper color with thin head; lace around glass; aroma of citrus; taste citrus/fruity;  Reminds me of Summer Shandy instead of an IPA but still fun to drink on a hot day.
12oz bottle; pours a dark amber; 1 finger head with lace that stays; smokey flavor; my first Scotch Ale.
12oz bottle;  Pours a golden color with a brief thin white head; aroma is fruity; a light flavored ale with a dry finish.
Label: Murphys Red Ale; 12oz bottle; pours a clear pale brown color; 1 finger head; aroma was hoppy;  watery in mouth; dry finish
12oz bottle; poured a dark walnut color with very little head; burnt caramel aroma; chocolate/coffee flavors which linger for a long time.
beer_name: JosephsBrau Black Toad Distinctive Dark Ale

review_blob: 12oz bottle; pours clear golden with 1 finger white head; not much aroma; bitter flavors that disappoint.  From Trader Joes
beer_name: Sea Dog Long Hot Summer Wheat Beer

review_blob: 12 oz bottle;  poured very dark clear copper color with a small off-white head; Lacing entire glass as I drank;  Aroma and taste of rye and with mild hops. well balanced; A rye beer that I will drink again.
